cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.COMM, cs.AR, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses achievable rate regions for WiFO using a novel coding technique, which falls under the domain of information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a new architecture for indoor wireless networks and discusses the integration of FSO with WiFi systems, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper discusses the use of FSO communication technologies and cooperative transmission frameworks to increase wireless capacity, which falls under the domain of communication and networking. 
4. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper discusses the femtocell architecture used in WiFO, which falls under the domain of hardware architecture. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper uses numerical and theoretical analyses to validate the proposed coding schemes, which falls under the domain of computational engineering.
